  "prompt": "Email to employer in Australia asking for 457 visa?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a professional and polite email template you can use to ask your employer in Australia for sponsorship under the 457 visa (note: the 457 visa was replaced by the Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) visa (subclass 482) in March 2018, so ensure you\u2019re referring to the correct visa):\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Request for Sponsorship for TSS Visa (Subclass 482)  \n\nDear [Employer's Name],  \n\nI hope this email finds you well. I am writing to formally request your support for sponsorship under the Temporary Skill Shortage (TSS) visa (subclass 482), formerly known as the 457 visa, to continue working with [Company Name].  \n\nOver the course of my employment with [Company Name], I have thoroughly enjoyed contributing to [specific achievements, projects, or responsibilities], and I am eager to continue bringing value to the team and the organization. Sponsorship under the TSS visa would allow me to legally remain in Australia and continue working in my current role, ensuring continuity and stability for both myself and the company.  \n\nI understand that the sponsorship process involves certain responsibilities and commitments from the employer, including nominating the position and meeting the required criteria. I have conducted research on the visa requirements and am happy to provide any necessary documentation or assistance to facilitate the process.  \n\nI truly appreciate the opportunity to work with [Company Name] and am excited about the prospect of continuing to contribute to the organization\u2019s success. I would be grateful for the chance to discuss this further and explore the possibility of sponsorship at your earliest convenience.  \n\nThank you for considering my request. Please let me know if you require any additional information or if there are any steps I can take to assist in the process.  \n\nLooking forward to your response.  \n\nBest regards,  \n[Your Full Name]  \n[Your Job Title]  \n[Your Contact Information]  \n\n---\n\n### Key Tips:\n1. **Be Professional:** Keep the tone polite and professional.  \n2. **Highlight Value:** Emphasize your contributions and commitment to the company.  \n3. **Offer Assistance:** Show willingness to help with the visa process.  \n4. **Check Visa Details:** Ensure you\u2019re referring to the correct visa subclass (482 instead of 457).  \n\nGood luck!",
